# Checkout & Orders Flows — Tradly Boilerplate

## Architecture

```
CheckoutPage (src/pages/CheckoutPage.tsx)
  │
  ├── Cart & summary        → useGetCartQuery (cartApi)
  ├── Addresses             → useGetAddressesQuery (addressesApi)       [auth only]
  ├── Storage hubs          → useGetStorageHubAddressesQuery (addressesApi)
  ├── Shipping methods      → useGetShippingMethodsQuery (shippingMethodsApi)  [two patterns]
  ├── Sub-shipment methods  → useGetSendCloudShipmentMethodsQuery       [conditional]
  │                           useGetExternalShipmentMethodsQuery        [conditional]
  ├── Payment methods       → useGetPaymentMethodsQuery (paymentMethodsApi)
  ├── Schedules             → useGetSchedulesQuery (schedulesApi)       [events/appointments only]
  ├── Cart commissions      → useGetCartCommissionsQuery (commissionsApi)
  ├── Demand commissions    → useGetDemandCommissionsQuery (commissionsApi) [auth only]
  ├── Coupon                → useApplyCouponMutation / useRemoveCouponMutation (cartApi)
  │
  └── Submit
        ↓ useCheckoutMutation (ordersApi) → builds { order: {...}, cart?: {...} } for SDK
        ↓
        Payment channel routing:
          stripe         → usePaymentIntentMutation → navigate('/payment')
          web gateways   → buildWebPaymentUrl → window.open(url)
          wallet / cash  → navigate('/thank-you/[order_reference]')
        ↓
  ThankYouPage  → /thank-you/:reference
  OrdersPage    → /orders
  OrderDetailPage → /orders/:id  → useGetOrderDetailQuery
```

---

## SDK Payload Structure

The SDK `checkout` call expects **nested** structure, not flat:

```
tradly.app.checkout({
  data: {
    order: {
      payment_method_id,
      shipping_method_id?,
      shipping_address_id?,     // authenticated delivery
      shipping_address?,        // guest delivery object
      external_shipping_method_id?,  // SendCloud / external
      type?,                    // checkoutType
      schedule_start_at?,       // "YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:00"
      schedule_end_at?,
      cart_commission?,         // [{ id, amount }]
      demand_commission?,       // [id, id, ...]
      anonymous_donation?,
      guest?,
      guest_email?,
      guest_name?,
      guest_phone?,
    },
    cart?: { id?, uuid? }       // uuid auto-injected by api/checkout.ts for guests
  },
  pkKey, authKey, currency, language
})
```

`api/checkout.ts` handles this transformation — it receives a flat `FullCheckoutPayload`
and wraps it as `{ order: orderFields, cart: cartRef }` before calling `buildAppMutationPayload`.
**Never manually construct `{ order: {...} }` in components — use `FullCheckoutPayload` instead.**

