## Shipping Methods — Two Patterns

Controlled by `AppConfig.enableShippingMethodsPreference` (`VITE_ENABLE_ACCOUNT_SHIPPING=true`).

```tsx
const useAccountShipping = AppConfig.enableShippingMethodsPreference
const sellerAccountId    = items[0]?.listing?.account?.id

// Pattern A — platform-wide (default): fetched immediately, no cart needed
const { data: tenantData } = useGetShippingMethodsQuery(
  { type: 'tenant', account_id: 0 },
  { skip: !needsShipping || useAccountShipping },
)

// Pattern B — seller-specific: fetched only after cart loads (needs sellerAccountId)
const { data: accountData } = useGetShippingMethodsQuery(
  { type: 'account', account_id: sellerAccountId },
  { skip: !needsShipping || !useAccountShipping || !sellerAccountId },
)

const shippingMethods = (useAccountShipping ? accountData : tenantData)
  ?.shipping_methods?.filter(m => m.active) ?? []
```

**Rules:**
- Only ONE of these two hooks fetches at a time (skip conditions are mutually exclusive)
- Pattern B waits for `sellerAccountId` — RTK Query auto-skips until it resolves
- Single-seller assumption: always uses `items[0]`'s seller

